(728, 'IE', 'Closed', '2024-07-15', '2099', 'IE-2024071501', 'Submission of C-40/50 Concrete mix design with steel fiber for approval for the treatment of the bridge pavement deck for the renovation of the existing (old) Bridge.\n', '?The submitted concrete mix design meets the requirement for the target mean strength of concrete cube at the site laboratory.\n?Concurrence is given for the C-40/50 concrete mix design using shear corrugated steel fiber.\nThis was shared with JV via email on July 16, 2024.', 'https://docs.qq.com/doc/DQ01HdFdvTWV4VkR3', 'Processing', 0, 0, 0, 0, 18, NULL, NULL),
(729, 'IE', 'Open', '2024-07-15', '3000', 'IE-2024071403', 'Submission of Repair of Cement Treated Base at Km 24+000 to 24+285 Service Road,LHS', '?The corrective action methodology has been reviewed and found non-compliant with what was agreed between Team Leaders, the Professor, and QCM from DBEDC.\n?The agreed corrective actions were to rebuild a monolithic 180 mm thick CTB layer where material had eroded or overlay with AC-20.\nSpecific agreed actions:\n1.Remove eroded pockets completely and relay with C15 grade concrete or CTB mix.\n2.Compensate mild surface erosion with a bituminous layer (AC-20) of additional thickness.\n?The agreed procedures were not followed, and the repair work is not acceptable (photos attached for reference).\n?The corrective action is not concurred, and further corrective measures are requested.\nThis was shared with JV via email on July 15 for taking necessary actions.', 'https://docs.qq.com/doc/DQ0ppd1ByT2FCYUls', 'Processing', 1, 0, 0, 0, 18, NULL, NULL),
(730, 'IE', 'Open', '2024-07-15', '3002', 'IE-2024071503', 'Partial closing of category 1. of NCR 49 & 50 (Deficiency in field core thickness and its strength in the cement stabilized gravel base pavement layer Km 11+500 to Km 12+468 Toll Road (LHS).\n', '?The corrective action report on NCR 49 and 50, submitted by the Project Company, was reviewed by the IE.\n?Consent for the corrective action was taken from the PD (RHD).\n?The corrective action for Category 1 includes adding 10 mm extra thickness to the design thickness of 40 mm on the AC 13-layer (i.e., 50 mm total thickness).\n?A review of documents and laboratory testing indicated thickness measurements of 40 mm to 41 mm instead of the designed 50 mm.\n?The NCR for Category 1 cannot be closed as no addition to AC-13 has been provided.\nIt is advised to submit further corrective measures to resolve the issue, ensuring the best attention at all times.\nThis wash shared with JV via email on July 16, 2024.', 'https://docs.qq.com/doc/DQ0xHWktRbkJaY3ZL', 'Processing', 1, 0, 0, 0, 18, NULL, NULL),
